{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0085707-55a3-4eb4-ac0b-afe29c3e7b5f","content":"Great news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in flag and is **no longer needed**. You can safely remove it.\n\n`EnableMSTestRunner` is still required — it builds your test project as an MTP-hosting executable.\n\nHere's the fix:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MGk8V3eLBHEUANJb9GPtiY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VYzBs6pmhpx2CYmpT3SiX2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7aadac2fd974437588ffa4a0753a9a06/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7aadac2fd974437588ffa4a0753a9a06/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"41359ca5-56b5-448a-b2aa-b949b5aec7ab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me look up what changed in .NET 10 regarding Microsoft.Testing.Platform and `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. This means:\n\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is **no longer needed** — it was a .NET 9 opt-in property that told `dotnet test` to use MTP instead of VSTest. In .NET 10, MTP is the default.\n\n\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required though — it ensures the test project compiles as an executable that can host the MTP runner. So they can safely remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property from their project file, but they'll want to keep `EnableMSTestRunner` in place.","outputTokens":553,"requestId":"3401:2F6FBA:758AD2D:81DE018:69F